I now have a complete understanding of the architecture. Here is the detailed implementation plan.

---

## Implementation Plan: Custom Theme System for T3 Code

### Architecture Overview

The design introduces three layers:

1. **Theme definitions** (`packages/shared/src/theme.ts`) -- pure data: type definitions, built-in theme objects, and lookup helpers. No React, no DOM, no Effect.
2. **Theme hook evolution** (`apps/web/src/hooks/useTheme.ts`) -- extends the existing `useSyncExternalStore`-based hook to store a named theme ID instead of "light"/"dark"/"system", apply CSS custom properties as inline styles on `document.documentElement`, and still toggle the `.dark` class for downstream consumers.
3. **Theme selector component** (`apps/web/src/components/ThemeSelector.tsx`) -- a self-contained UI component with preview swatches, integrated into the settings page.

---

### Step 1: Create `packages/shared/src/theme.ts`

This file uses plain TypeScript (matching the `model.ts` / `shell.ts` pattern -- no Effect, no Node.js imports). It defines:

**Types:**

```typescript
/** The IDs of all built-in themes */
export type ThemeId = "t3-dark" | "t3-light" | "t3-midnight";

/** The base color mode -- downstream consumers (terminal, diff, scrollbar) use this */
export type ColorMode = "light" | "dark";

/**
 * Every CSS custom property the app defines.
 * Values are raw CSS color strings (hex, oklch, rgb, etc.).
 * When a named theme is active, these are applied as inline
 * style properties on document.documentElement, overriding
 * the static :root / @variant dark definitions in index.css.
 */
export interface ThemeColors {
  background: string;
  foreground: string;
  card: string;
  cardForeground: string;
  popover: string;
  popoverForeground: string;
  primary: string;
  primaryForeground: string;
  secondary: string;
  secondaryForeground: string;
  muted: string;
  mutedForeground: string;
  accent: string;
  accentForeground: string;
  destructive: string;
  destructiveForeground: string;
  border: string;
  input: string;
  ring: string;
  info: string;
  infoForeground: string;
  success: string;
  successForeground: string;
  warning: string;
  warningForeground: string;
}

export interface Theme {
